Cook County Judge Dennis Porter cleared Officer Dante Servin in the March 2012 shooting death of Rekia Boyd . 
  He told loved ones to leave the courtroom before the verdict was read out . 
  Boyd was shot in the back of the head in Chicago in March 2012 . 
  She was unarmed and standing with friends when she was killed . 
  Officer Servin said he believed the shooting was an accident . 
  He was cleared of involuntary manslaughter and reckless discharge of a firearm . 
 